webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Next to Lake Nimmern, Oppeby Church is beautiful in the broken landscape. The present church building emerged in the mid-1700s by a desire in the parish for a more rigid house of worship in parallel with the need for a larger church room in a time of sharp population growth. Completely finished, the church stood in 1764, but was then already consecrated by Bishop Andreas Rhyzelius. The building to the west of the church still served at the time as the parish church school - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000027. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021018235639. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
